w.sfchronicle.com%2Ffood%2Frecipes%2Farticle%2Fcurried-cabbage-stew-toast-21270627.php%3Futm_campaign%3DCMS%2520Sharing%2520Tools%2520(Premium)%26utm_source%3Dshare-by-email%26utm_medium%3Demail%0A%0AThis%20gently%20spiced%20cabbage%2C%20sweet%20potato%20and%20white%20bean%20stew%20hits%20the%20sweet%20spot%20between%20nourishing%20and%20indulgent%2C%20especially%20with%20turmeric-chile%20butter%20toast%20on%20the%20side.%0A%0AThis%20message%20was%20sent%20via%20San%20Francisco%20Chronicle" class="y32px" aria-label="Share from Email"><svg width="32" height="32" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 33 33" class="p0 c-black td300 hover:o70"><circle xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" cx="16.0518" cy="16.75" r="15.375" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"></circle><path xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" id="Shape" fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M23.3018 11.75H9.80176C9.38754 11.75 9.05176 12.0944 9.05176 12.5192V20.9808C9.05176 21.4056 9.38754 21.75 9.80176 21.75H23.3018C23.716 21.75 24.0518 21.4056 24.0518 20.9808V12.5192C24.0518 12.0944 23.716 11.75 23.3018 11.75ZM11.4429 18.7566L13.6221 16.5774L11.4804 15.0575C11.3455 14.9618 11.3184 14.781 11.4197 14.6536C11.521 14.5263 11.7125 14.5006 11.8473 14.5963L16.5419 17.9279L21.2546 14.596C21.3896 14.5005 21.581 14.5265 21.6821 14.6541C21.7832 14.7816 21.7557 14.9624 21.6206 15.0578L19.5887 16.4944L21.7547 18.6604C21.8674 18.7731 21.8674 18.9557 21.7547 19.0683C21.6421 19.181 21.4594 19.181 21.3468 19.0683L19.1362 16.8578C19.1277 16.8493 19.1198 16.8403 19.1126 16.8311L16.7246 18.5194C16.6159 18.5962 16.4666 18.5961 16.3581 18.5191L14.0953 16.9133C14.0854 16.9276 14.0741 16.9412 14.0614 16.954L11.8509 19.1645C11.7382 19.2772 11.5556 19.2772 11.4429 19.1645C11.3303 19.0518 11.3303 18.8692 11.4429 18.7566Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></a></div></div></div><div></div><div class="b-gray500 bb pen mt16 col1Span row2 mb16 lg:gra"></div></section></div></div></div></div><div data-layout="Layout2ColumnPadded" class="f fdc lg:fdr lg:sx56 mx20 sm:mx32 xl:mxa xl:mw1200px mb20"><div class="mnw0 sm:px40 lg:px56 x100"><div class="package"><article class="rel"><figure class="rel f m0 fdc -mx20 sm:-mx40 lg:-mx56 x100vw sm:cw-80 lg:cw-112 mb32"><div class="rel x100 block"><picture><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1154px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1074px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1048px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_640.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_1080.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 784px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 768px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 768px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 720px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_768.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 640px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 480px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_640.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 360px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_480.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 240px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_360.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(max-width: 239px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_240.webp"/><img alt="Warmly spiced stew is paired with toast that’s slathered with seasoned butter. " loading="eager" fetchPriority="high" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_80.jpg 80w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_160.jpg 160w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_240.jpg 240w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_360.jpg 360w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_480.jpg 480w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_640.jpg 640w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_720.jpg 720w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_960.jpg 960w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_1080.jpg 1080w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_1440.jpg 1440w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744520/5/ratio4x3_1920.jpg 1920w" sizes="" style="aspect-ratio:4 / 3" class="x100 y100 opc bgpc ofcv bgscv block bg-gray200 mnh0px fill"/></picture></div><figcaption id="mediaCaptionAria" class="f fdc g2 rel pt8 px20 sm:px0 rel"><span class="photoCaption c-gray700 block ya"><div data-server-side-rendered="true" class="r12zgbl0 ruduv2y"><p>Warmly spiced stew is paired with toast that’s slathered with seasoned butter. </p></div></span><span class="photoCredit c-gray600 block rel z1 mt2 mr48"><span>Christian Reynoso </span></span></figcaption></figure><div class="pb20"><div id="everlit-auto-audio-widget" data-eid="item-102852" data-publication-id="pblc_kYW067sbmBR" style="height:130px" class="x100 tac fs16"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>There are some predictable cycles in the food media world. In the spring, everything on the plate must be green or have an egg involved. In the summer, it’s all about easy, fresh and staying away from the oven like it’s a bad idea. (The grill, however, is allowed.) Early fall is about getting back into a routine, whatever that means. Late fall through early winter turns cozy, sweet and very much about entertaining: what to bring, what to bake what will travel well.</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>Winter is also about coziness, but it’s layered with this idea of new beginnings. Maybe that means pulling back on alcohol, easing off overly rich foods or just wanting something that feels grounding again. I used to think predictions like this were constraining, like they boxed us in. These days, I think it’s helpful to have loose guides and themes to help us decide what feels right to put on the table when the days are short and we’re cooking a little more by instinct.</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>As for me, I keep coming back to balance. One night it’s pizza, the next it’s a big salad — sometimes it’s all on the same plate. With this week’s recipe, I’m firmly in the balance camp: a hearty vegetable stew paired with a big piece of butter-slathered toast.</p></div><div class="pt16 sy16 bb bt b-gray300 mb32"><div class=""><p class="uiHeader11 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="uiTextSmall f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="A300" data-large-id="CONCERT1" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="f jcc mnh250px sm:mnh600px ais lg:f lg:jcc lg:mnh300px lg:ais"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>The stew is warmly spiced, which brings depth and comfort, but it’s softened by sweet potato, tender cabbage and creamy white beans. Savoy cabbage, if you can find it, is especially good here. It’s leafy, crinkly, and vibrantly hued. When it simmers, it turns tender without losing its structure. I think of it as a young vegetable with an old soul.</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>Then there’s the toast. I prefer a thick piece of baguette, toasted in olive oil so it’s already rich before you even get to the butter. That butter is seasoned with earthy turmeric, bright lemon zest and crushed chile flakes for heat. It’s simple, but it does a lot. I highly recommend seasoning butter more often if you don’t already; it’s one of those small things that makes meals feel more intentional.</p></div><div class="mb32"><div class="x100 bg-white f fdc aic mxa p20 deep br4"><div class="f fdc aic mb10"><div class="f aic jcc"><div class="f aic"><div id="badge-logo"><svg width="50" height="50" viewBox="0 0 101 100" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="y100 bubi3gv" role="img" aria-label="San Francisco Chronicle Logo"><desc>San Francisco Chronicle Logo</desc><use href="#logosource-sfchronicle-badge"></use></svg></div></div><div class="pl10 pr10"><svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 14 13" class="p0"><path id="Path 5" d="M2.50195 2.00183L11.4983 10.9981" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"></path><path id="Path 5_2" d="M2.50195 10.9982L11.4983 2.00187" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"></path></svg></div><svg width="40" height="40" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="p0"><path d="M23.7449 12.27C23.7449 11.48 23.6749 10.73 23.5549 10H12.2549V14.51H18.7249C18.4349 15.99 17.5849 17.24 16.3249 18.09V21.09H20.1849C22.4449 19 23.7449 15.92 23.7449 12.27Z" fill="#4285F4"></path><path d="M12.2549 24C15.4949 24 18.2049 22.92 20.1849 21.09L16.3249 18.09C15.2449 18.81 13.8749 19.25 12.2549 19.25C9.12492 19.25 6.47492 17.14 5.52492 14.29H1.54492V17.38C3.51492 21.3 7.56492 24 12.2549 24Z" fill="#34A853"></path><path d="M5.52488 14.29C5.27488 13.57 5.14488 12.8 5.14488 12C5.14488 11.2 5.28488 10.43 5.52488 9.71V6.62H1.54488C0.724882 8.24 0.254883 10.06 0.254883 12C0.254883 13.94 0.724882 15.76 1.54488 17.38L5.52488 14.29Z" fill="#FBBC05"></path><path d="M12.2549 4.75C14.0249 4.75 15.6049 5.36 16.8549 6.55L20.2749 3.13C18.2049 1.19 15.4949 0 12.2549 0C7.56492 0 3.51492 2.7 1.54492 6.62L5.52492 9.71C6.47492 6.86 9.12492 4.75 12.2549 4.75Z" fill="#EA4335"></path></svg></div></div><h3 class="uiHeader8 tac fs18 mb12 sm:fs23 sm:uiHeader4"><div data-block-type="text" data-server-side-rendered="true" class="r12zgbl0 ruduv2y">See more S.F. Chronicle on Google</div></h3><div data-block-type="text" data-server-side-rendered="true" class="r12zgbl0 ruduv2y uiTextMedium tac c-gray700 mb16">Make us a Preferred Source to get more of our news when you search.</div><a href="https://www.google.com/preferences/source?q=sfchronicle.com" data-link="native" role="button" aria-label="Add Preferred Source" class="td300 cp f aic jcc disabled:cd wsn px24 y40px px16 py8 buttonSm fs13 xs:fs16 xs:buttonLg bg-primaryAccessible hover:o80 c-white disabled:bg-gray300 disabled:c-gray600 border bn tac br2"><div data-block-type="text" data-server-side-rendered="true" class="r12zgbl0 ruduv2y">Add Preferred Source</div></a></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>In the end, this soup might be a predictable recipe for the beginning of a new year. Honestly, it’s exactly what I want right now. And hopefully, you do too.</p></div><figure class="rel f m0 fdc -mx20 sm:mx0 x100vw sm:x100 p1h5oaun mb32"><div class="rel x100 block"><picture><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1260px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1186px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 1048px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_640.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 874px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 798px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 768px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_640.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 768px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_960.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 720px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_768.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 640px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_720.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 480px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_640.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 360px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_480.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 240px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_360.webp"/><source type="image/webp" media="(max-width: 239px)" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_240.webp"/><img alt="Spiced cabbage stew and a thick piece of buttery baguette: an ideal winter meal." loading="lazy" srcSet="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_80.jpg 80w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_160.jpg 160w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_240.jpg 240w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_360.jpg 360w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_480.jpg 480w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_640.jpg 640w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_720.jpg 720w, https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/55/51/55/28744521/5/ratio3x4_960.jpg 960w" sizes="(min-width: 1260px) 960px, (min-width: 1048px) 67vw, (min-width: 768px) 90vw, 100vw" style="aspect-ratio:3 / 4" class="x100 y100 opc bgpc ofcv bgscv block bg-gray200 mnh0px fill"/></picture></div><figcaption id="mediaCaptionAria" class="f fdc g2 rel pt8 px20 sm:px0 rel"><span class="photoCaption c-gray700 block ya"><div data-server-side-rendered="true" class="r12zgbl0 ruduv2y"><p>Spiced cabbage stew and a thick piece of buttery baguette: an ideal winter meal.</p></div></span><span class="photoCredit c-gray600 block rel z1 mt2 mr48"><span>Christian Reynoso </span></span></figcaption></figure><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><h2 class="cci_subhead" title="CCI Subhead">Curried Cabbage Stew with Turmeric-Chile Butter Toasts</h2></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p><em>Serves 4</em></p></div><div class="pt16 sy16 bb bt b-gray300 mb32"><div class=""><p class="uiHeader11 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="uiTextSmall f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="CONCERT1" data-large-id="CONCERT2" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="f jcc mnh250px sm:mnh300px ais lg:f lg:jcc lg:mnh300px lg:ais"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>This winter meal pairs tender vegetables in a savory, gently spiced gingery broth with very rich toast. It feels soothing and revitalizing, but still indulgent enough to feel satisfying.</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>If you can’t find Savoy cabbage (named for the Savoy region of France), green cabbage or Napa cabbage will work just fine. I suggest a curry powder that includes turmeric and garam masala, but if you have the individual spices and feel like mixing your own, I recommend it. The flavors will be brighter and more distinct.</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>2 cups diced sweet potato (from about 1 medium sweet potato)</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 medium yellow onion, diced small</p></div><div class="pt16 sy16 bb bt b-gray300 mb32"><div class=""><p class="uiHeader11 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="uiTextSmall f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="B300" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="f jcc mnh250px sm:mnh600px ais lg:none"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>4 large garlic cloves, thinly sliced </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1-inch piece ginger, finely chopped </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>Salt and pepper</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 tablespoon curry powder</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 small head (about 10 ounces) of Savoy or green cabbage, cored and roughly chopped</p></div><div class="pt16 sy16 bb bt b-gray300 mb32"><div class=""><p class="uiHeader11 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="uiTextSmall f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="CONCERT2" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="f jcc mnh250px sm:mnh300px ais lg:none"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>6 cups chicken or vegetable stock </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 (14-ounce) can white beans, drained and rinsed</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>6 tablespoons unsalted butter, room temperature</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>¼ teaspoon turmeric</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>¼ teaspoon crushed red chile flakes </p></div><div class="pt16 sy16 bb bt b-gray300 mb32"><div class=""><p class="uiHeader11 f aic jcc ttu">Advertisement</p><p class="uiTextSmall f aic jcc">Article continues below this ad</p></div><div data-block-type="ad" data-small-id="S300" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="f jcc mnh250px sm:mnh600px ais lg:none"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 lemon</p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>1 baguette, split in half lengthwise and toasted with olive oil </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p><strong>Cook the</strong> <strong>Curried Cabbage Stew: </strong>Heat the olive oil in a large size pot or Dutch oven over medium heat. Once the oil is warm, add the sweet potato, onion, garlic and ginger. Season with salt and pepper and stir. Cover with a lid and cook, lifting the lid to stir occasionally until the potato is fork tender and the onion is beginning to caramelize on the edges, about 8 to 12 minutes. </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p>Stir the curry powder into the vegetables and follow with the cabbage. Season the cabbage with salt, then stir and cook it until it wilts to half its volume, about 3 minutes. Pour in the stock and bring to a simmer. Simmer until the cabbage has completely wilted and some white parts turn a bit yellow, about 7 minutes. Add the white beans and simmer for 1 more minute. Turn the heat off and season with salt to taste.  </p></div><div><div data-block-type="ad" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="lg:none"></div></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p><strong>Make the Turmeric-Chile Butter:</strong> Meanwhile, add the butter, turmeric and chile to a small bowl and mix together with a fork. Finely grate in about half the lemon zest and season with salt. </p></div><div class="r1udwkp5 d1uy5mhj articleBody mb32" data-block-type="text" data-dropcap="false"><p><strong>Prepare the Toast:</strong> To serve, ladle the stew into bowls. Break the baguette into smaller pieces — I prefer large pieces, about ¼ of the total baguette — and toast. Spread the butter on the toast and place in the bowl with the stew. </p></div><div class="y1px x100 abs bgn top"></div><div style="top:25%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div style="top:50%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div style="top:75%" class="y1px x100 abs bgn"></div><div class="y1px x100 abs bgn bottom"></div></article></div><div class="package"><span class="mb16 block"><span class="smallTimestamp lg:largeTimestamp pb1 c-gray600"><time dateTime="2026-01-09 04:00:20">Jan 9, 2026</time></span></span><div><div class="py16"><div class="grid template-row2a temp-col-60px-1fr mnh100 g16 sm:g24"><div class="f fdc jcc xs:jcs xs:pt8 col1span3"><div class="primarySm mb2 xs:mb8">Christian Reynoso</div><div class="cardByline ttu c-gray600"></div></div><div class="row3 col1Span xs:row2 xs:col1span4 sm:col1Span xs:mt8 sm:mt0"></div><span class="col1Span xs:col4 xs:jsfe"><div class="sx8 f"></div></span></div></div></div><div></div></div></div><div class="none lg:f mnw300px x300px fdc g40 jcb"><div class="package y100 none md:block"><div class="s top97"><div data-block-type="ad" data-large-id="A300" data-unit="hnp-sfchronicle.com/article_dtc" class="lg:f lg:jcc lg:mnh600px lg:ais"></div></di